This paper deals with natural language processing (NLP) and specifically focuses on improving performance on reading comprehension tasks. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also uses recurrent neural networks (RNNs) and external annotations, which are common in sub-categories such as cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper deals with tasks that involve understanding and processing visual information, which could fall under sub-categories such as cs.CV (Computer Vision). Finally, the paper proposes a new recurrent layer, which could also be relevant to sub-category cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
